Mueller Report Exposes String Of Anonymously Sourced Stories That Got It Wrong | The Daily Caller
column8:
The Mueller report revealed a number of bombshell stories based on anonymous sources were apparently wrong. BuzzFeed and McClatchy each corrected two stories following the Mueller report‚Äôs release. Mueller‚Äôs report had no evidence backing up a bombshell report in The Guardian that went viral but has since come into question. A major CNN report on the June 2016 Trump Tower meeting was also inaccurate, Mueller‚Äôs report confirmed. Special counsel Robert Mueller‚Äôs report on Russian meddling revealed a string of anonymously-sourced stories about the investigation were inaccurate.
BuzzFeed and McClatchy each added editor‚Äôs notes to two stories following the publication of the Mueller report , which also contradicted an explosive CNN report and called into further question a bombshell story in The Guardian.
The Mueller report directly contradicted a Jan. 18 BuzzFeed story alleging that Mueller had evidence President Donald Trump ordered Michael Cohen, his former attorney, to lie to Congress about his exploration of a potential Trump Tower Moscow deal in 2016. (RELATED: Many Claimed Countless Times Over The Last 2 Years That Mueller Was ‚ÄòClosing In‚Äô ‚Äî Then He Filed His Report)
The story claimed that Cohen ‚Äútold the special counsel that after the election, the president personally instructed him to lie ‚Äî by claiming that negotiations ended months earlier than they actually did ‚Äî in order to obscure Trump‚Äôs involvement.‚Äù
But Mueller‚Äôs report states: ‚ÄúCohen said that he and the President did not explicitly discuss whether Cohen‚Äôs testimony about the Trump Tower Moscow project would be or was false, and the President did not direct him to provide false testimony. Cohen also said he did not tell the President about the specifics of his planned testimony.‚Äù
A June 2018 BuzzFeed story fingered former Russian Olympic weightlifter Dmitry Klokov as a potential go-between for Trump and Russian President Vladimir Putin.
Klokov was in contact with Donald Trump and Ivanka Trump, and offered to set up a meeting between Trump and Putin, the BuzzFeed report claimed, including photos of the weightlifter. Klokov at the time adamantly denied having been in contact with the Trump camp, and he was right.
Cohen had been in contact with a Russian he thought was Dmitry Klokov, the former Olympian, but he and BuzzFeed got it wrong. (RELATED: The Media‚Äôs Russia ‚ÄòBombshells‚Äô Look Even Worse Now That Mueller Found ‚ÄòNo Collusion‚Äô)
Mueller‚Äôs report showed Cohen had confused the Russian weightlifter with a former Russian official by the same name.
Cohen was still under the impression that he had been talking with the weightlifter when he spoke with the special counsel‚Äôs office, according to the Mueller report.
Michael Cohen, former attorney and fixer for President Donald Trump, arrives at the secure offices of the House Intelligence Committee in the basement of the House Visitors Center at the U.S. Capitol March 06, 2019 in Washington, DC. (Photo by Chip Somodevilla/Getty Images)
The Mueller report contained no evidence to support an explosive, but thinly sourced, article in The Guardian .
The Guardian‚Äôs article alleged that former Trump campaign chairman Paul Manafort visited WikiLeaks head Julian Assange three times between 2013 and 2016, including once around the time he joined Trump‚Äôs campaign.
The article, which was shared more than 100,000 times across the internet, attributed the bombshell claim to unnamed sources.
The Mueller report made no mention of Manafort ever visiting Assange. Before Mueller‚Äôs report came out, The Guardian‚Äôs story had been called into question.
Politico Magazine published an article the next day from a former CIA official who questioned if The Guardian‚Äôs reporters had fallen for ‚Äúa disinformation campaign.‚Äù
Two weeks after The Guardian‚Äôs story came out, The Washington Post‚Äôs Paul Farhi noted that the fact that no other outlet had confirmed the British paper‚Äôs story meant it ‚Äúcould be a dud.‚Äù More than five months after Farhi‚Äôs observation, The Guardian‚Äôs story remains unconfirmed.
When‚Äôs The Guardian and @lukeharding1968 updating their Manafort-Assange garbage story?
‚Äî Chuck Ross (@ChuckRossDC) April 19, 2019
The Daily Caller News Foundation emailed The Guardian‚Äôs press office to ask whether the paper has any plans to update, correct or retract its story, but did not receive a response by press time.
McClatchy, a news company with 29 newspapers under its umbrella, added editor‚Äôs notes to two Trump-Russia stories in response to the Mueller report‚Äôs release. (RELATED: NYT Corrects Story Claiming 17 Intel Agencies ‚ÄòAgree‚Äô On Russia)
Both McClatchy stories claimed that Mueller had evidence that Cohen traveled to Prague during the 2016 campaign, a key claim in the salacious but inaccurate Trump-Russia dossier.
The second report specified that Mueller had allegedly received evidence that Cohen‚Äôs personal cell phone sent signals to a tower near Prague in later summer 2016, around the time the dossier alleged that the former Trump fixer was meeting with a group of Kremlin insiders.
But Cohen hadn‚Äôt traveled to Prague, according to the Mueller report. ‚ÄúCohen had never traveled to Prague and was not concerned about those allegations, which he believed were provably false,‚Äù the report states.
When asked for comment, a McClatchy spokeswoman directed TheDCNF to an article the company published Thursday.
‚ÄúThe redacted report is silent on whether investigators received information placing one of Cohen‚Äôs devices in or near Prague, as McClatchy reported,‚Äù the article states, adding that ‚ÄúMcClatchy stands by the reporting.‚Äù
President Donald Trump walks to speak with supporters after arriving on Air Force One at the Palm Beach International Airport to spend Easter weekend at his Mar-a-Lago resort on April 18, 2019 in West Palm Beach, Florida. (Photo by Joe Raedle/Getty Images)
A bombshell CNN report on the June 2016 meeting that Trump Jr., Manafort and Jared Kushner attended with Russian nationals was flawed as well, Mueller‚Äôs report confirms. (RELATED: 7 Times CNN Botched The News In 2017)
The CNN story said that Cohen claimed ‚Äúthen-candidate Trump knew in advance about the June 2016 meeting in Trump Tower in which Russians were expected to offer his campaign dirt on Hillary Clinton.‚Äù
‚ÄúCohen alleges that he was present, along with several others, when Trump was informed of the Russians‚Äô offer by Trump Jr. By Cohen‚Äôs account, Trump approved going ahead with the meeting with the Russians,‚Äù the CNN report added, citing unnamed sources.
CNN stood by its story, even after Lanny Davis, Cohen‚Äôs attorney, refuted the network‚Äôs report . The Mueller report contradicted CNN‚Äôs reporting.
‚ÄúMichael Cohen recalled being in Donald J. Trump ‚Äòs office on June 6 or 7 when Trump Jr. told his father that a meeting to obtain adverse information about Clinton was going forward. Cohen did not recall Trump Jr. stating that the meeting was connected to Russia,‚Äù Mueller‚Äôs report states.
A CNN spokeswoman did not return an email seeking comment.

Electra started her career nearly three decades ago when she was still a teenager, and has appeared in several hit films such as ‚ÄúAmerican Vampire,‚Äù and several other horror films such as the ‚ÄúScary Movie‚Äù series, including ‚ÄúDate Movie,‚Äù and ‚ÄúMeet the Spartans,‚Äù and also starred in the television series ‚ÄúBaywatch.‚Äù
Electra has also had an incredible singing career, and is perhaps best known for her time as a member of the ‚ÄúPussycat Dolls,‚Äù an all-girl band that became popular in the early to mid 2000‚Äôs.
Electra has also modeled in magazines such as Playboy and Maxim. She‚Äôs had an incredible career and it‚Äôs only just getting started.
